<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Kill 16 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- At least 16 people were killed
and 12 injured in two traffic accidents in India's Punjab on
Saturday, Press Trust of India said today.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen people were killed and five injured when a Toyota car
collided head-on with a truck at around midnight on Saturday,
police said, adding that the injured were rushed to hospital.
</P>
<P>
In another mishap, two persons died and seven hurt when a jeep
collided with a tractor on Saturday night.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
