<DOCNO> XIE19970630.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails CPC's Role In Reunification (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, China's
leading newspaper, will publish an editorial Monday entitled "The
Force at the Core in Reunifying the Motherland and Invigorating
the Chinese Nation" to mark the 76th anniversary of the founding
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) that falls on on July
1. Excerpts of the editorial follow:
</P>
<P>
July 1 marks the 76th anniversary of the founding of the
Communist Party of China (CPC). It is also a day for China to
celebrate Hong Kong's return to the motherland and the end of 150
years of humiliation for the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong to the motherland has been the
aspiration for which countless people with lofty ideals had been
fighting and made sacrifices over the past more than 100 years but
failed to realize. It is only under the leadership of the
Communist Party of China that the century-old dream has been
materialized step by step. From the very day when the CPC was
founded, it made the independence, unification, democracy and
prosperity of the motherland its goal to fight for.
</P>
<P>
Since the Third Plenary Session of the 11th CPC Central
Committee in the late 1970s, the CPC has focused on
economic growth and introduced the reform and opening-up policy
while persisting in the four cardinal principles, preparing a solid
foundation and favorable conditions for the reunification of the
motherland and invigoration of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
The first generation of leadership of New China including Mao
Zedong and Zhou Enlai showed great concern for the Hong Kong
issue. With foresight, they put forward a series of major policy
decisions concerning the settlement of the Hong Kong issue.
</P>
<P>
The second generation of the central leadership, with Deng
Xiaoping at its core, used their super wisdom and boldness and
foresight to make the creative great conception of "one country,
two systems", making a major contribution to charting the best
course for promoting the great cause of peaceful reunification of
the motherland.
</P>
<P>
With indisputable facts, history reveals to the world that,
without the Communist Party of China (CPC), it would have been
impossible to have a socialist new China; neither would it have
been possible to materialize the return of Hong Kong to the
motherland.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970630.0003 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails CPC's Role in Reunification (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong marks the end of China's more than 100
years' history of humiliation and the starting point for putting
into practice the new conception. Placing before us are new
historical subjects of how to carry out unswervingly the principle
of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong", how to guarantee a high
degree of autonomy under the framework of "one country, two
systems," how to implement the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region and maintain a long-term prosperity and
stability of Hong Kong and go on to settle the Macao and Taiwan
issues in line with the same principles and ultimately realize the
great unity of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
The CPC is the force at the core for reunifying the motherland
and invigorating the Chinese nation. It is the fundamental
guarantee for making the Party greater and stauncher and for
continuing to push forward the great cause of reunifying the
motherland and invigorating the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
In order to further strengthen Party building, it is, first of
all, necessary to hold aloft the great banner of Deng Xiaoping's
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics and be
firm in adhering to the basic line of the Party for the primary
stage of socialism.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics is Marxism of contemporary China,
representing a powerful spiritual prop for invigorating and
developing the Chinese nation, as it has made a profound analysis
of and provides scientific answers to all major problems arising
in the drive for socialist modernization.
</P>
<P>
China's tremendous achievements in building socialism over the
past two decades since China's introduction of reform and
opening-up policy have eloquently proved that the theory conforms
to the realities of China and it is a scientific guide to the
efforts to invigorate the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's smooth return is another eloquent proof that this
theory conforms to the realities of China and it is a scientific
guide to the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
