<DOCNO> XIE19970630.0004 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails CPC's Role in Reunification (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The new situation in which the country is opening up to the
rest of the world and building a socialist market economy has made
it all the more necessary to strengthen the building of a clean
government and improve the Party style of work and to strengthen
the socialist spiritual civilization. The struggle against
corruption is a political struggle concerning the prestige of the
Party in the minds of the people, the close ties between the Party
and the masses of the people, the destiny of the Party, and the
long-term peace and stability of the country. The waging of the
anti-corruption struggle has won the support of the whole Party
and the people of the whole country. We must continue the struggle
with greater intensity and persistence. Leading cadres at all
levels must set an example, bear firmly in mind the fundamental
purpose of serving the people heart and soul, resolutely resist
the corrosion by such decadent ideas as money worship, hedonism
and individualism, display fully the fine tradition of hard work,
seek no fame and wealth, quietly immerse themselves in hard work
and make meritorious deeds to the Party and the people. Only by so
doing, is it possible to establish ourselves in an impregnable
position.
</P>
<P>
The CPC will call its 15th National Congress in the coming
autumn. The congress will be a historic grand gathering that will
bring the great cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, including the great cause of reunification of the
motherland, into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Let us, under the strong leadership of the Party Central
Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core and under the
guidance of the theory of Deng Xiaoping for building socialism
with Chinese characteristics and the Party's basic line, make
greater efforts to strengthen the unity of the Party, the unity of
the people of all nationalities of the country and the unity with
all the sons and daughters of the Chinese nation overseas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
