<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Gives Zimbabwe Nod for Batoka Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has given Zimbabwe the
green light to proceed with the Batoka hydro-electric scheme on
the Zambezi river estimated to cost 909 million U.S. Dollars,
Zimbabwean Transport and Energy Minister Simon Moyo said today.
</P>
<P>
Moyo said the Zimbabwean government is now looking for a
private partner to finance the scheme expected to have a power
output of 1,600 megawatts.
</P>
<P>
Zambia and Zimbabwe had in 1994 agreed in principle to jointly
build the power station which was expected to ensure reliability
of power supplies to both countries for over six decades.
</P>
<P>
But after careful consideration, the Zambian government has
decided that there are cheaper sources of power available
compared with the Batoka scheme. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
