<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Firm Issues Shares in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- A pharmaceutical company from the
northern municipality of Tianjin has become the first Chinese
company to issue and list shares in Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin Zhongxin Medicine Group Company, which specializes in
the production of Chinese medicine, Western medicine and
biological preparations, has issued a total of 100 million S
shares, which refer to those issued in Singapore, at a price of
0.68 US dollars per share.
</P>
<P>
The price/earning ratio, calculated on the basis of last year's
post-tax profit per share, was 8.8.
</P>
<P>
The latest issue, which is expected to raise 560 million yuan
worth of international capital, makes Singapore the fourth
overseas market where Chinese companies have listed shares. The
other three are Hong Kong, New York and London.
</P>
<P>
The pharmaceutical company is also the second firm from Tianjin
to issue shares overseas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
