<HEADLINE> Trade Between Jilin and Hong Kong Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Recent statistics show that Hong
Kong has become the seventh largest trade partner of northeast
China's Jilin Province, and a springboard for sending the
province's products into the Asian market.
</P>
<P>
By the end of April, Jilin's total trade volume with Hong Kong
had reached 300 million US dollars, and its transfer trade volume
via Hong Kong, 270 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is also one of the key overseas investors in Jilin;
the number of ventures in the province jointly-funded by Hong Kong
businessmen has reached 1,305, and about 300 local enterprises are
in business with Hong Kong partners, local officials said.
</P>
</TEXT>
