<HEADLINE> DPRK Congratulates on Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Central People's Committee of
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) sent Chinese
President Jiang Zemin a message of congratulation on Hong Kong's
return to the motherland on July 1.
</P>
<P>
In its message, the Central People's Committee called Hong
Kong's return to the motherland "a historic event, which ends the
disgrace imposed on Chinese people by foreign powers."
</P>
<P>
"It proves the correctness of the 'one country, two systems'
principle proposed by the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
Chinese government," the message said.
</P>
<P>
The committee also expressed its joy over China's resumption of
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and its sincere hope for
greater successes made by the Chinese people in achieving
prosperity and national reunification under the leadership of the
CPC with Jiang at its core. 
</P>
