<HEADLINE> Museveni Meets British Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- President Yoweri Museveni today
met British Minister of State for Foreign and Commonwealth
Affairs Tony Lloyd here and discussed with him bilateral issues.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, they also discussed regional issues
including the situation in the Great Lake region, a source here
said.
</P>
<P>
Steven Nabeta, the Permanent Secretary in Ugandan Ministry of
Foreign Affairs and the British High Commissioner in Uganda were
present at the discussions.
</P>
<P>
Lloyd who arrived in Uganda Saturday from Kenya is accompanied
by Director of Africa in his office Richard Dales.
</P>
<P>
During his African trip, Lloyd will end his visit to Uganda
this evening and his visit in the continent will include South
Africa later. 
</P>
