<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Leaders Congratulate on HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Bandaranaike Kumaratunga and Prime Minister Sirimavo Ratwatte Dias
Bandaranaike have respectively telegraphed congratulations on Hong
Kong's return to China to their Chinese counterpart Jiang Zemin
and Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
"All Sri Lankans welcome this resumption of China's sovereignty
over that territory, in the confident expectation that it cannot
but accrue to the enhanced well-being of both" China's inland
areas and Hong Kong, said the Sri Lankan president.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan prime minister believed that Hong Kong's return
to China forecasts prosperity and happiness of the Chinese people
including Hong Kong people in the future.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, which has been under the British colonial rule for
more than a century, is due to return to the motherland on July 1,
1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
