<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Launches Amphibious Military Exercise in Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian navy forces today
launched an amphibious military exercise in the Persian Gulf
in a bid to enhance combat readiness.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the four-day
war game was jointly carried out by the naval forces of
the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC) and the army of the
Islamic Republic of Iran.
</P>
<P>
However, the short report gave no detail about the number
of forces and weapons to be used in the war game.
</P>
<P>
Major-General Mohsen Rezaee, Commander of the Islamic
Revolution Guard Corps (IRGC), said in an interview carried in
today's English daily Kayhan International that any U.S. military
 adventurism against Iran would be crushed and called on foreign
military forces in the Persian Gulf to get out the region.
</P>
<P>
Rezaee is believed to replace current Defense Minister
Mohammad Forouzandeh in the new government headed by Mohammad
Khatami, who won a landslide victory in the 7th presidential
election on May 23.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian general attacked the United States for seeking
to destabilize the region, adding "they want to keep the
regional states under pressure and threats. They create threats
to maintain their presence otherwise they can in no way
justify their presence.
</P>
<P>
However, he sent a message to Americans: "the Persian Gulf
is our region. They have to leave our region. We have vital
interests in the Persian Gulf and we are going to defend
interests."
</P>
<P>
On the issue of possible military confrontation between Iran
and the United States, he said, Iran will never start any
war. But if the Americans one day decide to attack us, then they
would have committed suicide.
</P>
<P>
"We will turn the region into a slaughterhouse for them.
There is no place better than the Persian Gulf to destroy
the Americans' might," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, the Americans are after a military confrontation
with Iran.
</P>
<P>
Rezaee noted that the presence of foreign powers, especially
American forces, in the Persian Gulf, is tantamount to an
aggression against the region. "It is against international
norms and it creates instability in this region."
</P>
<P>
"Iran is committed to protect security in the Persian Gulf
and is trying with patience to get foreign forces out of
this region," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
