<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Leaders Congratulate on HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi President Shahabuddin
Ahmed and Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina have respectively
telegraphed congratulations on Hong Kong's return to China to
Chinese President counterpart Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed, who called the return a "historic occasion," believed
that "the new chapter in history marked by this occasion will
contribute to peace and stability in the region and bring greater
prosperity and progress for the people of China and the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region."
</P>
<P>
"The people of Bangladesh share the happiness and joy of the
Chinese people in celebrating this historic occasion," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hasina said the historic event will not only bring "greater
prosperity and well-being for the Chinese people " but also "
further the cause of peace and prosperity in the region."
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, which has been colonially ruled by Britain for more
than a century, is due to return to its motherland at midnight on
June 30, 1997. 
</P>
