<HEADLINE> Licenses of 17 NGOs Revoked in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Disaster Prevention and
Preparedness Commission of Ethiopia today announced here that the
licenses of 17 non-governmental organizations have been canceled
for failing to begin operation in the country.
</P>
<P>
In a statement quoted by the Ethiopian News Agency, the
commission said although it has announced through mass media
earlier that non-governmental organizations should present
evidences for beginning operation, the stated number of
non-governmental organizations did not give responses.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, the non-governmental organizations
whose licenses have been revoked included the Southern Ethiopian
Peasant Development Aid, Development Innovatives Promotion and
Sustainability Assurance Program of Ethiopia, Harvest Family Spot
Organization and African Humanitarian Action.
</P>
<P>
The commission called on government agencies, private
organizations and donors to refrain from assisting the stated
organizations as they have no more recognition across the nation.
</P>
</TEXT>
