<HEADLINE> Cambodian King Congratulates on HK's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk
today sent a message of felicitations to Chinese President Jiang
Zemin, congratulating on Hong Kong's return to the motherland on
July 1.
</P>
<P>
Sihanouk said in the message that he and his government would
like to extend warmest congratulations to Jiang, the Chinese
government and people and formulate sincere good wishes for the
continuous prosperity and well-being of the people of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"On this auspicious occasion, we recall that the people of Hong
Kong are able to return to their motherland thanks to the wisdom
and clear-sighted policies" initiated by the late Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping, and by his eminent successors led by President
Jiang Zemin and by Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
He said that Cambodia will always strongly support the complete
territorial integrity and unity of China. "In this regard, we
formulate sincere good wishes for the prompt national
reunification and return of Taiwan to China while looking forward
to the return of Macao, in 1999, to the motherland," he said.
</P>
