<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June, 29 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh, Macedonian, Moldovan,
Tajik, Turkish and Yugolav leaders have sent messages of
felicitations to Chinese leaders, congratulating on Hong Kong's
return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev said in his message to
Chinese President Jiang Zemin that Hong Kong's return is a great
success for China and the Chinese people in their years of
struggle to bring historical justice.
</P>
<P>
He expressed wishes for China's prosperity and development
after Hong Kong's return as well as new achievements in the
national reunification.
</P>
<P>
Kazakh Prime Minister Akezhan Kazhegeldin said in a message to
Chinese Premier Li Peng that he is confident that the Chinese
people, inspired by this significant event, will achieve great
success in the country's social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov said China would achieve
greater progress in its development after Hong Kong's return on
July 1, which is "the triumph of justice."
</P>
<P>
Moldovan President Peter Luchinsky welcomed China's policy of
realizing national reunification and territorial integrity by
peaceful and civilized means.
</P>
<P>
He said Moldova supports the efforts by the Chinese government
to solve the issues of Taiwan and Macao as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
In a message to Jiang, Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov said
that Hong Kong's return is a historic event at the turn of the
century.
</P>
<P>
Turkish President Suleyman Demirel also said in a message to
Jiang that he is confident that under the "one country, two
systems" principle, Hong Kong would continue to further flourish,
adding new dynamism to the Chinese economy.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia Radoje
Kontic said in a message to Premier Li Peng that he is confident
the Chinese policy based on the "one country, two systems" concept
will prove to be viable and contribute significantly to the
country's overall development and preservation of its unity and
stability. 
