<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in Tanzania Holds Film Reception </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Embassy in Dar
es Salaam today held a film reception to celebrate the return of
Hong Kong to China.
</P>
<P>
Attending the reception were more than 150 people, including
Tanzanian government officials, diplomatic envoys and officials
of the embassy as well as representatives of Chinese expert teams
and companies based here.
</P>
<P>
During the reception, the film "Opium War" was shown and
it was warmly received by the audience.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Chinese ambassador to Tanzania Xie Yuokun said at the
reception that as the return of Hong Kong is at hand, the Chinese
people all over the country including 6.3 million compatriots in
Hong Kong are filled with exultation and are greeting, in various
ways, the advent of the date of great historic significance --
July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
"It is our firm belief that by adhering to the policy of 'one
country, two systems' and with the strong support of her
motherland China, Hong Kong, the bright pearl of Orient, will
certainly embrace an even brighter future tomorrow," the Chinese
ambassador said. 
