<HEADLINE> African Leaders Congratulate China on Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of Niger, Sudan and South
Africa have sent their congratulations to Chinese President Jiang
Zemin on China's resumption of exercise sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Niger's President Ibrahim Barre Mainassara said China's
resumption of exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong is a historic
event, which sets an example in peaceful solution of regional and
international issues and shows China's desire to maintain peace
and security in the world.
</P>
<P>
Sudan's President Omar Hassan Ahmed el-Bashir in his letter of
felicitation spoke highly of China's efforts for Hong Kong's
return to the motherland on July 1, 1997, and its steadfast
determination for Macao's return in 1999 and the national
reunification in the near future.
</P>
