<HEADLINE> Thai PM Congratulates China on HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh Friday sent a message of congratulations on China's
resumption of exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
"The handover of Hong Kong to the People's Republic of China is
an important historical occasion for China, and I am very pleased
that the handover process has proceeded smoothly," the prime
minister said in his message.
</P>
<P>
He said that he believes under the Chinese government's policy
of "one country, two systems," Hong Kong will sustain its distinct
dynamism and further develop as an economic center.
</P>
<P>
With the growing friendship between China and Thailand, "I am
also certain that the relationship between Thailand and Hong Kong
will be further enhanced through mutual cooperation and
support ..." the prime minister said. 
</P>
