<HEADLINE> India PM Congratulates China on HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister Inder Gujral
sent a message of congratulations to his Chinese counterpart, Li
Peng, over Hong Kong's return to the motherland on July 1.
</P>
<P>
In the message, the prime minister described the return as a
final end to colonial rule in Asia. He said that Indian people,
who shared the same experience of having been oppressed by
colonialism in the past, can fully understand the joy of the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, as an important international trade and financial
center, played a unique role in promoting trade and economic
cooperation between China and India, the prime minister said,
adding that he believes the maintenance of Hong Kong's prosperity
after July 1 would continue benefit the interests of China and
India. 
