<HEADLINE> World FMs Congratulate China on HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministers of Argentina,
Bangladesh, Colombia, Cyprus, Poland and Vietnam today sent
messages of felicitations respectively to Chinese Vice Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen on Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued today, Argentine Foreign Minister Guido
Di Tella said that Hong Kong's peaceful return to the motherland
has set an example for the international society.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the "one country, two systems" principle,
saying that the principle would help maintain the current economic
system and life style in Hong Kong and facilitate exchanges so as
to promote China's development.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Argentine government would like to deepen
relations with China in all fields and to maintain trade and
economic ties with the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
In a message to Qian Qichen, Bangladeshi Foreign Minister Adbus
Samad Azad described Hong Kong's return as a historic event for
the Chinese people, which would usher in a new era full of hope
and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Colombian Foreign Minister Maria Emma Mejia said in the message
to Qian that Hong Kong's return on July 1 would make commitment
made in the Sino-British Joint Declaration implemented.
</P>
<P>
She said the great event would have profound impact on the
international society, because it shows disputes between countries
could be solved through negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Cypriot Foreign Minister Ioannis Kasoulides also said that Hong
Kong's peaceful return to China is a turning-point in
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Polish Foreign Minister Dariwsz Rosati said he believed that
the historic event would not only help keep Hong Kong's important
status as an economic center in the region but also improve Hong
Kong's prosperity and well-being of its people.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam said in a message
to Qian that Hong Kong's return to the motherland marks the end of
more than one hundred years of British colonial rule there. It
represents a great success of the Chinese government's "one
country, two systems" principle and is in line with China's
national conditions and interest.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen Manh Cam also said that Vietnam believes cooperation
between China and Vietnam, as well as Hong Kong and Vietnam, would
be further strengthened. 
</P>
