<HEADLINE> Chinese TV Show Week Held in Cameroun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, June 29 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese TV show week has been
going on in Cameroun to celebrate Hong Kong's return to China on
July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by Cameroun National Television Station (CRTV) in
collaboration with the Chinese embassy here, six Chinese color
documentary films, namely "The Great Wall", "Hong Kong of China",
"Cross 1997 -- Hong Kong Toward Future", "China", "Beijing Toward
the Outside World" and "Shatoujiao -- a Little Town Between
Guangdong and Hong Kong", will be shown during the golden show
time in the evenings of the week starting Friday on CRTV.
</P>
<P>
These documentary films depict what Hong Kong is like in the
past and present, explain Chinese government's policy regarding
Hong Kong after its return to the motherland, which is "One
Country, Two Systems". The films also tell objectively what has
happened in China, especially its great achievements made in the
recent 18 years.
</P>
<P>
The CRTV will make another two special programs to introduce
Hong Kong's history, its social and political situation as well
as its economic development and its people, giving Camerounians a
full sense of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The show week started on June 27 and will draw the curtains on
July 2. 
</P>
