<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian PM Urges Military Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 30 (Xinhua) -- With national security in mind,
Russia's armed forces should be reformed urgently, Russian Prime
Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to military academies' graduates in the Kremlin,
Chernomyrdin said military reform was aimed at making the armed
forces not only compact and mobile, but also efficient and
equipped with the most modern armaments and technical means, a
Itar-Tass report said.
</P>
<P>
Russia needs a strong army with high combat effectiveness, the
prime minister said. There still existed many problems concerning
the country's military security.
</P>
<P>
