<HEADLINE> 2.4 Mln Apply for Voting in Bosnian Local Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, June 30 (Xinhua) -- About 2.4 million Bosnians have
applied for voting in the upcoming municipal elections, the
Organization of Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) reported
today.
</P>
<P>
OSCE spokesman David Foley said the number, which is still
initial, is the same as the turnout in the national elections in
September 1996.
</P>
<P>
