credited the OSCE voter education efforts and various political
parties for mobilizing potential voters to register.
</P>
<P>
The voter registration was originally arranged for six weeks,
but due to low turnout through much of the process, it had to be
prolonged for two more weeks until June 28.
</P>
<P>
In Brcko, a strategic area claimed by both Serbs and Muslims,
the voter registration had to be restarted after instances of
voter manipulation were found and would last until July 12.
</P>
