National Union for Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) to
cooperate with UN observers in speeding up examiniations on its
policing troops in the diamond mining area.
</P>
<P>
According to UN resolutions, UN observers' mission on Angola
will start operation at 0:00 am on July 1 for a 7-month tenure.
</P>
<P>
The number of observers' mission, Beye noted, will be smaller
than that of the Rectification Mission.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the withdrawal of UN peacekeeping forces in
Angola, the envoy said, it's up to the situation in Angola.
