<HEADLINE> OPEC Supervised Oil Price Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The average package price of seven
supervised oil products of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries last week showed a slight increase reaching 17.15
U.S. dollars per barrel, say statistics issued by the OPEC
secretariat today.
</P>
<P>
The average oil price two weeks ago was 16.94 U.S. dollars per
barrel.
</P>
<P>
The OPEC ministerial meeting last week asked its member states
to strictly abide by their own daily quota so as to maintain the
OPEC daily quota of 25.03 million barrels to stabilize the world
oil price.
</P>
<P>
The average oil price of OPEC dropped to 18.76 U.S. dollars
per barrel in May from 23.06 dollars in the first quarter. The
stipulated OPEC oil price was set at 21 dollars per barrel.
</P>
