<HEADLINE> WTO 1998 Conference Scheduled for Mid-May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The World Trade Organization (WTO)
announced today that its biennial ministerial conference will be
held on May 18-20, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The 131-member WTO is expected to make use of the occasion to
celebrate the 50th anniversary of the multilateral trading system,
WTO officials told a press briefing.
</P>
<P>
Since the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT) took
effect in 1948, world trade has increased 16 fold and is predicted
to increase 22 fold by 1998, WTO figures show.
</P>
<P>
At the 1998 conference, WTO officials will review the
achievements of GATT and WTO in past years and discuss ways the
organization can adapt to the challenges of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The latest WTO ministerial conference was held in Singapore on
December 9-13,1996. 
