<HEADLINE> Chinese President, Premier Meet with British PM in HK (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Jiang said that he believed Hong Kong would become
more prosperous and stable after its return to China, and this
should be attributed to Deng Xiaoping's great concept of "one
country, two systems".
</P>
<P>
"We had proceeded from the overall strategic situation of
stabilizing the world situation and creating a long-term peaceful
international environment, and taken into account Hong Kong's
history and current situation and the interests of various
quarters, before we formulated a series of policies for resolving
the Hong Kong question," he noted.
</P>
