<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tiananmen Gala for Hong Kong's Return Sets Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Tiananmen Square is welcoming a
sea of 100,000 jubilant partygoers who have gathered here to
celebrate the return of Hong Kong to the motherland with endless
forms of merry-making.
</P>
<P>
Among tonight's activities are several record-setting firsts,
biggests and bests ever to take place on the square. They include:
</P>
<P>
Biggest Lanterns
</P>
<P>
Upon entering Tiananmen Square, one of the most spectacular
sights is the glow of 160 giant red lanterns hung high around the
square. One hundred of the lanterns have been placed along both
sides of the digital countdown clock in front of the Museum of
Chinese History, symbolizing Hong Kong's return to the motherland
after more than 100 years.
</P>
<P>
The 100 red lanterns are the biggest ever to decorate the
square: 40 of them are 2.6 meters in diameter and 4.22 meters high.
</P>
<P>
Lengthiest Gala
</P>
<P>
The gala event, called the "Beijing Municipal Government
Greeting Hong Kong's Return Evening Party," started at 10 p.m. on
June 30 and will last seven hours and 15 minutes. It will be
longest celebration held in the square since the founding of New
China in October 1949.
</P>
<P>
Biggest Drum
</P>
<P>
The beating of 100 drums will be heard throughout this
evening's activities. One of the drums measures 3.03 meters in
diameter and 0.97 meters high, and is believed to be the biggest
drum in China. Six young boys standing on stools will beat the
instrument.
</P>
<P>
The drum was made specially for the party by five brothers in
Baimashi County, in the city of Luoyang, central China's Henan
Province. It will be donated to the Federation of Literary and Art
Circles after the event.
</P>
<P>
First Time Fireworks Launched in Center of Square
</P>
<P>
Standard practice has it that fireworks in Tiananmen Square are
launched from the top of high buildings surrounding the
area. Tonight, three rounds of fireworks were set off from the
central square region.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Guanchen, a police official in charge of the fireworks
displays, said this is the the first time that fireworks have been
launched from this spot.
</P>
<P>
First Stage in Square
</P>
<P>
The stage erected in front of the Monument to the People's
Heroes is the first stage to be set up in Tiananmen Square since
New China's founding.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 actors, actresses and amateur performers are
participating in a variety of shows on the bi-level stage, which
covers 1,225 square meters.
</P>
<P>
First Large Color TV Screens
</P>
<P>
Five large color TV screens have been set up on the square to
provide live coverage of the handover ceremonies in Hong
Kong. Again, a first for super-sized TVs on the square.
</P>
<P>
The largest is 4.8 meters high and eight meters wide.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
