<HEADLINE> Chinese President, Premier Meet with British PM in HK (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
and Premier Li Peng met with British Prime Minister Tony Blair at
the Harbor Plaza Hotel in Hong Kong this evening.
</P>
<P>
"Premier Li Peng and I are very glad to meet with you at this
historic moment of Hong Kong's handover," President Jiang said to
Prime Minister Blair.
</P>
<P>
Blair said that this evening is of historic significance for
China, Britain and Hong Kong, and with the close of an old chapter
in the Sino-British relations, a new page will be opened as a new
starting point for the development of the relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
He added that Hong Kong should also become a bridge in the
Sino-British bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang said that it is very important to develop a
friendly and cooperative relationship between China and Britain
and to increase mutual understanding and trust.
</P>
<P>
"We always believe that as long as both sides can follow the
basic principles of mutual respect, equal treatment, seeking
common ground while reserving differences and non-interference in
each other's internal affairs, a long-term and stable relationship
of mutually beneficial cooperation can be established and
developed," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
With the 21st century around the corner, he said, leaders of
China and Britain should be far-sighted and regard the
Sino-British relationship as a matter of strategic importance
which can affect the overall global situation in the next century.
</P>
<P>
With the settlement of the Hong Kong question, the labor
government should have no burden in developing the relationship
between the two countries, he told Blair.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that he believed a new chapter will be opened in the
Sino-British relationship with the joint efforts of both sides.
</P>
</TEXT>
