<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 122.35 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market today gained 122.35 points to
reach 4,256.09 as against last Friday's close of 4,133.74.
</P>
<P>
The National Index also showed a hefty rise of 57.10 points to
1,827.43 from the previous close of 1,770.33.
</P>
<P>
Speculatives spurted sharply, pushing the sensitive index on
the BSE market today to a new 52-week high of 4,256 on the opening
day of the new account in the wake of hectic buying and aggressive
purchases by Foreign Institutional Investors (FIIs).
</P>
<P>
The index-based heavy weighted blue chips like Hind Lever, ITC,
MTNL, Tata Steel, ACC and Steel Authority scored impressive gains.
GA cement was the day's favorite on rumors that the company might
announce a liberal bonus issue.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said the market had gone up only because of FIIs buying
and any adverse news would lead to sharp correction as the gains
were already overextended.  
</P>
</TEXT>
