<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Night-long Carnival To Welcome Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- All Beijing is lit up, but no
place more so than Tiananmen Square where 100,000 citizens have
gathered for a long night of celebrations which will continue
until dawn.
</P>
<P>
Just a few hours before China resumes its exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong, Tiananmen Square and adjacent
buildings were illuminated by floodlights while the dark summer
sky was brightened by fireworks galore.
</P>
<P>
"In about two hours, the return of Hong Kong to the motherland
will come true. It will be the solemn time for the Chinese nation
to wash away their humiliation of the past century, the brilliant
time for them to open up a new historical era, and the great time
for hundreds of millions of the Chinese people to march towards
unification and prosperity," Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin said at
around 10:00 p.m. on the gala night.
</P>
<P>
Performances are being held on two separate stages on the
square. On the central stage, beside the digital countdown clock,
a musical titled "Beijing Bless You, Hong Kong" is going on.
</P>
<P>
People are dancing and singing national favorites in an
explosion of patriotic fervor.
</P>
<P>
Six huge light-boxes are positioned in the center of the
square, bearing the characters "Celebrating Hong Kong's Return to
the Motherland".
</P>
<P>
As midnight approaches, five huge screens around the square
will provide revellers with live coverage of the handover ceremony
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Activities will continue until the national-flag-raising
ceremony at 4:50 a.m. on July 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
