<HEADLINE> Advance PLA Troops Enter HK to Take up Defense Duties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- A 509-member advance party of
the People's Liberation Army Garrison arrived in Hong Kong at 9
p.m. today.
</P>
<P>
The entry of the advance troops this evening is in compliance
with an agreement previously reached between the two sides of the
Sino-British Joint Liaison Group.
</P>
<P>
Together with the three other advance groups, the PLA men in
Hong Kong now number 705.
</P>
<P>
A defense handover ceremony between Chinese and British troops
is scheduled for the midnight today at the Tamar Barracks, and the
PLA advance troops will take up defense duties at zero hour on
July 1.
</P>
<P>
When the advance troops in 39 military vehicles drove to the
Huanggang Customs Checkpoint for Hong Kong earlier today, they
were cheered by more than 10,000 local well-wishers waving fresh
flowers and colorful ribbons lining the road to show their respect
for the well-disciplined troops.
</P>
<P>
Before passing through the customs, Major General Xiong Ziren,
political commissar of the PLA Hong Kong Garrison, said that the
entry of the PLA troops is symbolic of the Chinese government's
resuming the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and will
provide a guarantee for Hong Kong's long-term prosperity and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
"We are resolved to always bear our mission in mind, live up to
the high expectations placed on us, perform the defense duties of
Hong Kong in accordance with law, and make our contributions to
Hong Kong's long-term stability and prosperity," he said.
</P>
<P>
The advance troops which arrived this evening will be
stationed in the barracks at Tamar, Stanley, Stonecutters Island
and Shek Kong Camp.
</P>
<P>
At zero hour on July 1, the advance troops and other advance
parties will simultaneously hoist China's five-star red flag over
all the 14 barracks taken over by the PLA Garrison.  
</P>
</TEXT>
