<HEADLINE> URGENT: Chinese President, Premier Meet with Blair in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
and Premier Li Peng met with British Prime Minister Tony Blair in
the Harbor Plaza Hotel at Hung Hom, Kowloon, at 8:25 pm today.
</P>
<P>
This is the first meeting between top Chinese and British
leaders in Hong Kong and also the first meeting between the heads
of government of the two countries since 1992.
</P>
<P>
At press time, the meeting is still in progress.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen and
British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook are present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng arrived here by
special plane at around five o'clock this afternoon to attend the
Hong Kong handover ceremony at midnight today.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that top Chinese leaders have ever set
foot on this part of Chinese soil, which was under the British
colonial rule over the past one and a half centuries.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Tony Blair also flew into here earlier today.
</P>
</TEXT>
