<HEADLINE> Edwards P1ulls out of IAAF Grand Prix Meets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Britain's world triple jump record
holder Jonathan Edwards has withdrawn from two Grand Prix meetings
this week with a heel injury.
</P>
<P>
Edwards will miss the meetings in Lausanne on Wednesday and
Oslo's Bislett Games on Friday.
</P>
<P>
He first felt the effects of the problem at the recent European
Cup in Munich, where he restricted himself to only two jumps when
winning his speciality in Britain's overall team victory.
</P>
<P>
The injury continued to trouble him last week but world
champion Edwards took the decision to compete in Sunday's meet at
Sheffield as a mark of respect to his supporters.
</P>
<P>
But after producing a second round clearance of 17.54 meters to
win the competition ahead of Olympic champion Kenny Harrison of
the United States, he took no further part in the competition.
