<HEADLINE> Egyptian FM: Hong Kong Return Makes History </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa today termed as historic and epoch-making event the return
to China of its once-lost Hong Kong, the Egyptian Middle East
News Agency (MENA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian top diplomat, who is in Hong Kong to attend the
celebrations marking the return of Hong Kong to the motherland of
China, said China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong " ends a problem that had been triggered off in the
middle of the 19th century."
</P>
<P>
After 156 years of colonial rule by the United Kingdom, Hong
Kong returns to China at midnight today in a harborside ceremony
with the swearing-in of a new chief executive and a provisional
legislature.
</P>
<P>
In statements to the MENA, Moussa said Egypt looks forward to
boosting flourishing trade, economic and investment ties with
Hong Kong, which is among the key trade zones in the entire world.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has already signed agreements to facilitate trade with
the once-British-occupied territory, including allowing Hong Kong
citizens to enter Egypt without entry visas, Moussa said.
</P>
</TEXT>
