<HEADLINE> ANAP Leader Becomes Turkish Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Center-right Motherland Party
(ANAP) Chairman Mesut Yilmaz announced here today that he has
become the prime minister of Turkey's 55th government.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz made this announcement at the presidential palace at
noon after President Suleyman Demirel approved a cabinet list
for the coalition government consisting of the ANAP, Democratic
Left Party (DSP) and Democratic Turkey Party (DTP).
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz submitted the cabinet list to Demirel for approval
following talks with his coalition partners this morning.
</P>
<P>
He said that DSP leader and former Prime Minister Bulent
Ecevit became deputy prime minister and DTP deputy Chairman and
former parliamentary speaker Ismet Sezgin serves as deputy prime
minister and national defense minister. 
