<HEADLINE> Writethru: Chinese President Arrives in HK for Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
heading a Chinese government delegation, arrived here this
afternoon by special plane.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China and chairman of the Central Military
Commission, is here to attend the Hong Kong handover ceremony at
midnight today.
</P>
<P>
At about five o'clock this afternoon, two special planes with
the Chinese government delegation on board landed at the Kai Tak
International Airport one after another.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang and Chinese Premier Li Peng emerged from the
cabins and waved to the cheering crowd braving a heavy rain on the
tarmac.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that top Chinese leaders have ever set
foot on this part of Chinese soil, which was under British
colonial rule over the past one and a half centuries.
</P>
<P>
Stepping on the red carpet, Jiang and Li were presented flowers
by four teenagers.
</P>
<P>
Several hundred people from various walks of life in Hong Kong
waved Chinese national flags, regional flags of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) and flowers to greet the
arrival of the Chinese leaders.
</P>
<P>
They were greeted at the ramp side by Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen, who also a member of the Chinese government
delegation had arrived here earlier, Director of the Xinhua News
Agency Hong Kong Branch Zhou Nan, Chief Executive of the HKSAR
Tung Chee Hwa and principal officials of the HKSAR government.
Jiang and Li shook hands and exchanged greetings with them one by
one.
</P>
<P>
British Minister of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs
Derek Fatchett was also on hand.
</P>
<P>
Also arriving were members of the Chinese government
delegation, including Wang Hanbin, Zhang Wannian, Fei Xiaotong,
Lei Jieqiong, Cheng Siyuan, Wu Jieping, Luo Gan, Wu Xueqian, Dong
Yinchu, Ma Man-kei, He Luli and Zhuo Lin.
</P>
<P>
Other members of the 72-strong delegation came here from
Shenzhen by car earlier today.
</P>
<P>
After the welcoming ceremony, Jiang Zemin and Li Peng were
driven to their residence at the Harbor Plaza Hotel in Kowloon.
</P>
<P>
The fact that a high-level delegation with extensive
representation headed by President Jiang Zemin came here to attend
the handover ceremony has drawn wide attention of the
international community.
</P>
<P>
It is generally agreed that this reflects the utmost importance
the Chinese government attaches to the return of Hong Kong, as
well as the determination of the central government to
unswervingly implement the basic principles of "one country, two
systems", "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and a high degree
of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the handover ceremony, President Jiang Zemin will
also head the central delegation at a ceremony marking the
establishment of the HKSAR and the swearing-in of the HKSAR
government and a grand celebration for the establishment of the
HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng will also meet with
Prince Charles, British Prime Minister Tony Blair and dignitaries
from various countries attending the handover ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
