<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Hails Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Iran today hailed the return of
Hong Kong to China, which falls midnight tonight, describing it as
a very important development in the political scene of the world
and a great success for China.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Abbas Maleki said at a
ceremony held here to celebrate Hong Kong's return to China that
"we again witness that a page in the history of colonization has
been turned over and China enters a new era of its political life."
</P>
<P>
"I seize this occasion to congratulate the Chinese government
and people for this historical event," he said in his address to
300 diplomats, government officials and representatives of various
circles at the ceremony hosted by the Chinese Embassy in Iran.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Iran Wang Shijie, said on the occasion
that July 1, 1997, will be a big day in the history of China. The
Chinese government will resume the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong and wipe out the disgrace brought on China about
one-and-a-half century ago.
</P>
<P>
Ala'eddin Boroujerdi, Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister for
Asia-Pacific Affairs said Sunday that the event is an end to
one of hundreds of examples of British colonialism in the world
and Iran is pleased with such a great success.
</P>
<P>
He said that the time of colonialism exerted by world powers
has come to an end and the nations now in every corner of the
world stand up against any kind of oppression.
</P>
<P>
Iranian press today also devoted large coverage to the return
of Hong Kong to China by carrying news stories or editorials.
</P>
<P>
English daily Iran News said that China will get its own
territory back after 156 years and the Chinese people have every
reason to be delighted on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Tehran Radio criticized Britain for its rule
over Hong Kong, saying that the return of Hong Kong to China
signaled the end of the British Empire.
</P>
<P>
The radio predicted that Hong Kong would turn into a shinning
star of China due to its powerful economy. The return of Hong
Kong to China will have positive effects on the People's
Republic of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
