<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Hails HK's Return (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the moment when the whole nation celebrates Hong Kong's
homecoming, it should be kept in the minds of all the tortuous
paths that the Chinese people have gone through towards the
historical day, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
-- For the day to come, millions of heroic sons and daughters
of the Chinese nation struggled against colonial rule and resisted
foreign aggression unyieldingly, and in wave upon wave, to defend
their national dignity and maintain the integrity of the country's
sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
However, due to the weakness and impoverishment of the country
and the decadence and incompetence of its governments in the old
days, generations of patriots in history failed in their struggle
to accomplish their lofty aspirations.
</P>
<P>
-- For the day to come, after the founding of the People's
Republic of China, the Chinese Central Government has constantly
announced that Hong Kong has been an inseparable part of China's
territory since ancient times, that China does not recognize the
three unequal treaties imposed by the British imperialists, and
that this historical question should be peacefully settled through
negotiations at an appropriate time. They also stated that Hong
Kong's status quo should be maintained before a solution is
achieved.
</P>
<P>
New China's first generation of leaders, including Mao Zedong
and Zhou Enlai, paid full attention to the future of Hong Kong and
formulated a series of strategic policies on the Hong Kong issue,
which has contributed to Hong Kong's stability and prosperity, and
laid a solid foundation for the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
After the reform and opening-up policy was implemented in 1978,
China entered a new period of development and has rapidly improved
its comprehensive strenghth and its status in the international
community with a most invigorating image. This has provided the
solid basis for negotiating Hong Kong's smooth return.
</P>
<P>
-- For the day to come, the Chinese government, in its quest
for national unity as well as the stability and prosperity of Hong
Kong, put forward the proposal of "one country, two systems." The
proposal has provided practical means to solve the issues
of Hong Kong, Taiwan and Macao, and for the eventual reunification
of the country.
</P>
<P>
Practice has showed the principles of "one country, two
systems" and "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" are in the
best interests of the Hong Kong people, and they have gained wide
support from both people in Hong Kong and China's inland areas
as well as approval of the international community.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says now "one country, two systems" is being
widely acclaimed as a theory of broad vision and a work of great
creativity in the history of civilization.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970630.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily's Editorial Hails Hong Kong's Return (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When celebrating the return of Hong Kong, the editorial says,
we cherish a deep memory of esteemed Comrade Deng Xiaoping. As a
great revolutionary, patriot and the chief architect of China's
reform and opening up drive, he took liberation, revitalization
and reunification of the motherland as his main responsibilities
throughout his life.
</P>
<P>
At the core of the second generation of China's collective
leadership, he creatively put forward the great proposal of "one
country, two systems" with rare political courage, broad
open-mindedness and supreme wisdom, thus playing a significant
role in securing the smooth process of Hong Kong's return to the
motherland. The "one country, two systems" proposal will be
recounted in the country's history as one of Comrade Deng
Xiaoping's most significant contributions to the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
The editorial attributes Hong Kong's return to the leadership
of the Communist Party of China (CPC), the great achievements of
reform and opening up, the unremitting efforts of three
generations of China's leadership and especially to Deng
Xiaoping's theory of building a socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
This is the solemn conclusion that we draw from history, the
editorial says.
</P>
<P>
However, the return of Hong Kong is just an initial step being
taken to implement the "one country, two systems" guideline. It is
more important now to guarantee the long-term prosperity and
stability of Hong Kong. The Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China provides
the fundamental guarantee in this respect.
</P>
<P>
The editorial calls on people from both Hong Kong and the
inland areas to study and strictly abide by the Basic Law. It
expressed the hope that Hong Kong people will assume the
responsibility of governing Hong Kong with a high sense of being
the master in the house, so as to administrate and build Hong Kong
in an efficient way.
</P>
<P>
Now, under the guidance of the basic theories and lines of the
CPC and the leadership of the CPC Central Committee with Jiang
Zemin at the core, the country enjoys political stability,
economic growth, national unity and social development, it says.
</P>
<P>
The world can expect to see a brighter future for China. With a
5,000-year-old history of civilization, the Chinese nation will
stride ahead with pride into the new century toward the
magnificent goal of modernization. The reunification of China and
the revitalization of the Chinese nation will become a glorious
fact in the future, the editorial says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
