<HEADLINE> ASEAN Opens Conference on Civil Service Matters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The 9th ASEAN Conference on
Civil Service Matters (ACCSM) opened here today, with "ASEAN Civil
Services - Sharing and Learning for the 21st Century" as its
theme.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening of the conference, Lee Ek Tieng, head
of the Singapore Civil Service, said that with the next millennium
being labeled as the Pacific Century, the civil services should
take advantage of the opportunities in the region and help create
the condition for growth, thereby raising the living standards of
the people.
</P>
<P>
"The ACCSM presents an excellent platform for maximizing the
synergy to be harnessed from within ASEAN (the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations) as well as with friends of ASEAN," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The intention of the theme at the current conference "is to
reinforce the need to share and learn from each other as we
embrace new challenges," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The ACCSM is held once every two years with the objective of
bringing about closer cooperation among the civil services of
ASEAN countries and to strengthen and equip them to meet the
challenges of the current rapid development taking place in ASEAN
and the world.
</P>
<P>
The present conference, which will conclude on Friday, is being
attended by delegates from the seven ASEAN member countries --
Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Thailand, Singapore
and Vietnam -- and is being observed by delegates from Laos,
Myanmar, Australia, Canada, India, Japan, New Zealand and Russia.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
