<HEADLINE> Patten Bids Farewell to Government House </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 -- Christopher Patten, the 28th as well as
the last Governor of Hong Kong, bid farewell to the Government
House, his residence in Hong Kong, this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The farewell ceremony started at 4:20 p.m. local time at the
Government House in Hong Kong's Central District, which was built
in 1855 and has been the residence for 25 governors of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
At 4:30 p.m., the Governor's standard in front of the house was
lowered and presented to Patten, a standard procedure for
departing governors.
</P>
<P>
At 4:40, Patten and his family left for the last time the
Government House where they have lived for the past five years.
</P>
<P>
After 156 years of colonial rule over Hong Kong, Britain is to
hand it back to China at midnight today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
