<HEADLINE> Over 8,500 Ugandans Daily Infected with HIV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Over 8,500 people are infected
with HIV virus daily in Uganda, the local daily "The Monitor"
said today.
</P>
<P>
Yusuf Kibuuka Nsubuga of the Ugandan AIDS Commission was
quoted as saying that in recent years, people infected with the
HIV virus in Uganda have increased to 1.9 million.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a workshop on HIV/AIDS Transmission and Prevention
here on Saturday, Nsubuga noted, a national AIDS documentation
and information center is being developed at the Uganda AIDS
Commission.
</P>
<P>
Nathen Bakyayita, an official in Ugandan Ministry of Health
said on the same occasion that 84 percent of AIDS infections
occurred through unprotected sexual intercourse in the country,
with 25-40 percent of children population contracting HIV/AIDS
from infected mothers.
</P>
<P>
Although aids awareness is between 95-99 percent in Uganda,
said Bakyayita, behavioural change has not yet taken place.
</P>
</TEXT>
