<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Approves First Gold Refinery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has approved investment
license to the first gold refinery plant in the country,
according to a latest statement released by the Zambia Investment
Center.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that about four million US dollars will be
spent in establishing the gold refinery by Milkwood Ltd., a
company jointly owned by two South African and two British
nationals, to purchase, assay and refine precious metals
including gold, silver, platinum, rhodium and palladium.
</P>
<P>
This investment will make Zambia the second country in Africa
to have a gold refinery after South Africa, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Milkwood Ltd. is expected to purchase precious metals in
Zambia and from the region and to refine them for the export
market.
</P>
<P>
The investment comes after some foreign companies heightened
their gold prospecting activities last year in Ndola rural of
Copperbelt province.
</P>
<P>
"Zambia's strategic position on the regional market as well as
its good economic environment influenced Milkwood Limited's
choice of the country as the location of the investment," a
partner of the company was quoted by the statement as saying.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
