<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
rallied strongly today, hitting another eight-year high, with the
market index topping the 2,500-point mark for the first time since
1989.
</P>
<P>
The rally followed big gains on Friday prompted by the Reserve
Bank governor's statement that he preferred easing the monetary
conditions.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 59 points higher at 2,502 with a
turnover of 132 million NZ dollars (88 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Market leader New Zealand Telecom led the rises, whose shares
jumped 30 cents to 750 and accounted for one-quarter of the
turnover. Also higher were Carter Holt Harvey, climbing 13 cents
to 381; Air New Zealand, up 6 cents to 308; Brierley Investment 4
cents to 144; and Lion Nathan, 2 cents to 373.
</P>
<P>
But Fletcher Challenge shares failed to join in the rally with
Building, Energy and Paper all steady at 443, 445 and 357 cents
respectively. Only Fletcher Forests edging up 1 cent to 214.
</P>
</TEXT>
