<HEADLINE> URGENT: Seven Killed in Bomb Explosion in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 30 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were
killed and more than 40 others injured when a bomb exploded in a
bus in Pakistan's southern city of Sialkot, known for its exports
of sports goods.
</P>
<P>
Informed sources said the bus was packed with about 100 local
workers going for duties. Among the seven killed were women and
children.
</P>
<P>
The injured have been sent to nearby hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Further details about the explosion were not immediately
available. 
</P>
