<DOCNO> XIE19970630.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister Meets with Albright in HK (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the bilateral relations, Qian and Albright agreed that both
the Chinese and U.S. governments attached utmost importance to the
Sino-U.S. relations, and that maintaining and developing a sound
and stable Sino-U.S. relationship is not only in the interest of
the two countries, but also conducive to peace and stability in
the Asia-Pacific region and the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
They were of the view that thanks to efforts by both sides, the
Sino-U.S. relationship has been generally good over the recent
period, with more exchanges and contacts between the two sides and
continued development in economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have also cooperated in a number of
international and regional issues, they added.
</P>
<P>
They held that all this showed the two countries' consensus on
establishing a cooperative relationship that will continue in the
21st century, and a foundation had been laid for further
development of the Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
Qian and Albright also held that it is of great significance
for the heads of state of China and the U.S. to exchange state
visits, which will inject new vitality to the development of the
bilateral relations and open a new chapter in the Sino-U.S.
relations.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that both sides should continue to make joint
efforts and active preparations, and that officials of relevant
departments in the two countries should make more contacts and
consultations to reach some consensus and agreements in the
political, economic and trade fields so as to ensure the success
of Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen stressed that the Taiwan question remains the most
important and sensitive issue in the Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
Albright said that the U.S. would continue to observe the three
joint communiques between the two countries and keep to the "one
China" policy.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also exchanged views on other questions of
common concern.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice Foreign Minister Wang Yingfan was present at the
meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
