<HEADLINE> Salvador Ties U.S. 1-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The United States and El
Salvador played to a 1-1 tie on Sunday at a CONCACAF World Cup
qualifying match in El Salvador.
</P>
<P>
The draw left the Americans (1-3-1) alone in third place with
six points in the six-team, final round of CONCACAF qualfying.
</P>
<P>
El Salvador improved to 1-2-2 and fourth place, the leader of
three teams with five points.
</P>
<P>
Mexico leads with 11 points, followed by Costa Rica with
seven. The top three qualify for the World Cup finals in France.
</P>
<P>
The home team attacked fiercely throughout before a home crowd
of 38,000 at Cuscatlan Stadium while the U.S. squad played a
defensive game with only one striker.
</P>
<P>
However, the visiting team opened the scorings 51 minutes into
the match through Roy Lassiter, who found the net between two
Salvadorian defenders.
</P>
<P>
Raul Diaz Arce pulled back 10 minutes later on a ball rebounded
off of a defender. 
</P>
