<HEADLINE> Sweden Edges Russia 2-1 in European Women Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Anna Pohjanen scored the game
winner with eight minutes remaining to lift Sweden to a 2-1
victory over Russia on Sunday, the opening day of the European
Women's Soccer Championship.
</P>
<P>
France and Spain drew 1-1 earlier in the day to open the
eight-nation tournament, which finishes with the title game on
July 12 in Oslo, Norway.
</P>
<P>
The event is being played in Norway and Sweden.
</P>
<P>
At Karlstad, Sweden, before a crowd of 3,829, Hanna Ljungberg
put Sweden ahead the in the 10th minute, a lead which held until
Larissa Savina tied in the 80th.
</P>
<P>
Pohjanen became the hero for the Swedish team, which finished
runner-up in the 1995 tournament to Germany.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, in Karlskoga, Angelique Roujas scored in the 50th
minute to give France the draw before only 920. Maria Jimenez gave
the Spaniards the lead in the 14th minute.
</P>
<P>
The tournament continues Monday with the opening games in Group
B in Norway, where Germany plays Italy and Denmark takes on world
champion Norway. 
