<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forty Sri Lankan Rebels Killed In Navy Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan navy destroyed four
Tamil rebel boats off the lagoon of Kokilai in the Northern
province, killing 40 rebels including two of their regional
leaders on Sunday morning, military sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The navy also caused heavy damage to two other rebel boats
during the confrontation. One boat got away.
</P>
<P>
The military believed that the rebel boats were carrying
medical requirements for the rebels of the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) from Vakarai to Mullaitivu area, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been waging a 14-year guerrilla war against the
Sri Lankan government for a separate Tamil state in the north and
east of the island country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
