<DOCNO> XIE19970630.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Beats Germany in Euro Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Zoran Savic scored a game-high 16
and Alexander Djordjevic added 14 points Sunday to lift the
defending champion Yugoslavia to 88-73 victory over Germany in the
second round of the European Basketball Championship.
</P>
<P>
Nikola Bulatovic and Dejan Tomasevic came off the bench to
score 12 and 11, respectively, for Yugoslavia, which improved to
2-1 in Group F.
</P>
<P>
Teams carry first-round results from common opponents into the
second round of the 16-nation tournament, which ends on July 6.
</P>
<P>
In other games Sunday, Poland rallied from a 28-point halftime
deficit to shock Croatia 77-76. Elsewhere at Badalona in Group F,
Italy edged Spain 63-60. In Group E in Girona, Turkey downed
Israel 81-71; Russia beat France 93-80; and Greece edged Lithuania
73-66.
</P>
<P>
Italy moved to the top of its group with an unbeaten record and
six points, with Russia one behind and followed by Lithuania,
Israel and Turkey. Italy topped Group F with six points, with
Yugoslavia and Spain a point behind. The top four in each after
two more games qualify for the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
In consolation round games at Badolona, Slovenia topped Bosnia
73-61 while Ukraine beat Latvia 84-76. Slovenia and Ukraine will
play for 13th place on Monday while Latvia and Bosnia will play
for 15th. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
