<HEADLINE> Bailey Beats Christie Over 150 Meters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The first world 150-meter champion
Donovan Bailey of Canada win the distance again on Sunday, this
time he beat Linford Christie over the same 150-meter distance
outdoors in Sheffield of England.
</P>
<P>
Bailey collected the winner-take-all prize of 50,000 pounds
(about 82,500 U.S. Dollar) as a bonus. His first 150-meter win
over Michael Johnson of the United States last June brought him a
total of 1.5 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The world and Olympic champion and world record holder for 100
meters clocked 15.01 running into a headwind to leave the former
Olympic titlist well back in third place behind another Britain
Ian Mackie.
</P>
<P>
The Bailey-Christie confrontation over the rarely run distance
was supposed to be the high point of the Securicor Games at the
Don Valley stadium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
