<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Following are highlights of
today's major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Today's paper devotes six pages to stories and pictures
hailing Hong Kong's return to the motherland, as the countdown
clock ticks ever closer to the zero hour at midnight tonight.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said yesterday at a ceremony
bidding farewell to the Chinese Government Delegation on its trip
to Hong Kong that the central government will firmly support HKSAR
in exercising its rights vested by the Basic Law and safeguard the
Hong Kong residents' right and freedom in accordance with the law.
</P>
<P>
As head of the delegation, Jiang also said before leaving for
Hong Kong that the delegation's trip to Hong Kong demonstrates the
close unity of all nationalities and patriots in China and their
joy at HK's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
-- The paper publishes a commentary hailing the role played by
the Communists Party of China (CPC) in the nation's reunification
process today, to mark the 76th anniversary of the founding of the
CPC that falls on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The commentary says from the very day when the CPC was founded,
it has made independence, unification, democracy and prosperity of
China its goal to fight for. It adds that the CPC is the force at
the core for reunifying the country and invigorating the Chinese
nation.
</P>
<P>
-- To welcome the 15th National Congress of the CPC in the
coming autumn, today's paper devotes a whole page to articles on
how to enhance and improve the building of the party in various
state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- China's inland areas during the past days have made full
preparation for celebrating the upcoming Hong Kong's return to the
motherland, and the whole nation is now excited by the historical
event and filled with patriotism.
</P>
<P>
-- The Standing Committee of the 8th National People's
Political Consultative Conference (NPPCC) closed its 21st session
yesterday in Beijing. Li Ruihuan, chairman of NPPCC presided over
the meeting and made a speech.
</P>
<P>
-- Some 800 representatives and guests from more than 40
countries and regions, and more than 30 international and regional
organizations will attend the Hong Kong handover ceremony at
midnight on June 30.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A front page article says that the historic return of Hong
Kong to the motherland will benefit HK's economy. The paper
quotes a top local trade coordinator as saying that now Hong Kong
is ready to step into the future and place its trust and economy
in the welcoming arms of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
-- The People's Liberation Army Hong Kong Garrison is now fully
prepared to shoulder the defence responsibilities over Hong Kong,
the paper quotes sources from the troops as saying.
</P>
<P>
-- The paper devotes four full pages to Hong Kong Focus, which
carries interviews with heads of major Chinese banks, insurance
companies, stock exchanges and trade officials on the future of
Hong Kong as an international financial center and eocnomic ties
between Hong Kong and the inland areas after the handover. 
</P>
</TEXT>
