<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Holds Seeing-off Rally for PLA Hong Kong Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China held a grand rally here
this morning to see off the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA)
troops to be stationed in the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
General Fu Quanyou, member of the Central Military Commission
(CMC) and chief of the PLA General Staff, read out the order by
Jiang Zemin, chairman of the CMC, on the troops' entering and
stationing in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqing, member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and vice
chairman of the CMC, asked the 4,000-strong officers and men of
the HKSAR garrison to carry out their defense duties in accordance
with law and fulfill all tasks successfully.
</P>
<P>
Liu reviewed a guard of honor made up of men of the ground,
naval and air forces of the troops at the beginning of the rally,
which was attended by more than 6,000 people including senior
officials from central military departments, central government
departments and local governments, and local civilians and troops.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at the rally, Liu said that the stationing
of PLA troops in Hong Kong is a significant symbol of China's
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong, and also
an important guarantee for safeguarding the national sovereignty
and security and for maintaining Hong Kong's prosperity and
stability.
</P>
<P>
He urged the troops to unswervingly carry out Deng Xiaoping's
great conception of "one country, two systems" and enhance their
sense of duty and sense of responsibility for safeguarding Kong
Kong's prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
He called on the officers and men of the HK garrison to bear in
mind the principle of serving the people whole-heartedly and be
loyal to the party, the motherland, the people and socialism.
</P>
<P>
Liu stressed that the troops should tighten its own management
in a strict way, carry out their duties in accordance with law,
abide by discipline strictly and never commit even the slightest
offense against the civilians.
</P>
<P>
It is also necessary for the troops to strengthen cultural
development, make great efforts to enhance military training and
improve their comprehensive quality, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
The troops are surely capable of inheriting and developing the
fine traditions of the PLA and always maintaining the good image
of the PLA as a mighty, civilized force in line with Deng
Xiaoping's thought guiding army building in the new period and
Jiang Zemin's expositions on army building, he said.
</P>
<P>
He believed that the troops will surely live up to the great
expectations placed upon them and fulfill their duties and tasks
in Hong Kong successfully.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant General Tao Bojun, commander of the Guangzhou Area
Command, also asked the troops to firmly carry out the order by
Chairman Jiang Zemin so as to ensure safe and smooth entering and
stationing in Hong Kong on scheduled.
</P>
<P>
Lu Ruihua, governor of the Guangdong province, and Li Youwei,
secretary of the Shenzhen Municipal Committee of the Chinese
Communist Party, expressed in separate speeches that local
governments and people will go all out as before to support the
troops as a powerful backing and reliable rear, and make
contributions to the long-term prosperity and stability of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Major General Xiong Ziren, political commissar of the troops,
said on behalf of all officers and men that they will keep in mind
their tasks, always be loyal to the motherland, strictly perform
their defense duties, safeguard the sovereignty and dignity of the
motherland and maintain the long-term prosperity and stability of
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
General Shi Yuxiao, political commissar of the Guangzhou Area
Command, presided over today's seeing-off rally.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
