<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Meets with U.S. Secretary of State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen met here this morning with U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Albright is here to attend the Sino-British Hong Kong handover
ceremony at midnight today.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that he was very glad to meet with Albright in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
"We talked about the Hong Kong question when I visited
Washington two months ago," said Qian. "And now we are having a
meeting here."
</P>
<P>
Albright said she and her entourage were quite glad to be here
for the handover, an event she acknowledged as an important
historical moment for China.
</P>
<P>
She extended congratulations to China and pledged that the
United State has always supported and will continue to support
Hong Kong's prosperity and stability.
</P>
