<HEADLINE> International Observers Satisfied With Albanian Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The multinational force's guiding
committee said here this evening that it is satisfied with the
proceeding of the Albanian election held today.
</P>
<P>
In a communique, the committee said the poll has been generally
peaceful and hoped that all the contesting parties will respect
the election results and rebuild their country in the spirit of
national reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
The committee has been monitoring the voting in Albania and has
kept in touch with the 238 international monitoring groups through
an electronic communications system and a video-conferencing
system in the Italian Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Under the escort of the multinational troops, the monitoring
groups kept supervision over 3,570 polling stations or 80 percent of
the total. 
</P>
