<HEADLINE> Chinese Enterprises Sponsor Post-Doctoral Studies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Major enterprises and 20
universities in China have jointly established centers for
post-doctoral studies to produce high-level research workers,
education sources said.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 post-doctoral researchers now working in nine such
centers have conducted well over 100 hi-tech projects in a wide
range of scientific fields, such as metallurgy, machinery,
petroleum, computer science, and mining.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Baoshan Iron and Steel Group and Shanghai Jiaotong
University set up the country's first joint post-doctoral station
in 1994. Liu Wenyu, the first to complete post-doctoral studies
there, achieved outstanding results in automated control after two
years and is now a leading researcher in the enterprise.
</P>
<P>
The station has enrolled 12 graduates from three famous
universities to pursue post-doctoral studies.
</P>
<P>
To attract more researchers to the stations, the enterprises
are providing satisfactory working and living conditions for
them.  
</P>
</TEXT>
