<HEADLINE> Pak, China Have Special Friendly Relationship: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and China have a
special friendly relationship, nurtured by successive Governments
here, and there is complete national consensus on maintaining this
relationship.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made here this evening by Mushahid Hussain,
Advisor to the Prime Minister on Information and Culture, at a
seminar on Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
He congratulated the Chinese people and Chinese leadership on
Hong Kong's return to her motherland on behalf of the Pakistani
government.
</P>
<P>
Pak-China ties are a model for relations between two neighbors
and Pakistan fully stands by its friend, Mushahid said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion, Javed Ibrahim Piracha, member of the
National Assembly, said the historic occasion was symbolic of
Chinese wisdom and thinking.
</P>
