<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets with British Foreign Secretary in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen met this morning with British Foreign
Secretary Robin Cook at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center.
</P>
<P>
Both Qian and Cook are here to attend the Sino-British Hong
Kong handover ceremony at midnight today.
</P>
<P>
As it was raining here this morning, Cook said that he
apologized for the bad weather he had brought from Britain.
</P>
<P>
Qian replied that he believed that the weather would be fine
tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
By press time, the meeting is still in progress.
</P>
