<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats Bolivia 3-1 in Copa America Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Brazil scored 3-1 final
victory over Bolivia Sunday en rout to capturing its fifth Copa
America soccer title in La Paz of Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo's goal gave Brazil a 2-1 lead and Ze Roberto added the
finale three minutes into injury time.
</P>
<P>
It was the first South American title for Brazil since 1989,
and the first time in 11 finals away from home that it was able to
win and bring the trophy home.
</P>
<P>
The first goal came unexpectedly when Roberto Carlos fired a
free kick that bounced off Carlos Trucco. Denilson tracked down
the ball and scored by bouncing it off Edmundo.
</P>
<P>
The Bolivians protested saying Edmundo was offside.
</P>
<P>
The equalizer also came unexpectedly, when Sanchez launched a
30-meter rocked past Brazilian keeper Claudio Taffarel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
