<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Celebrate Hong Kong's Homecoming With All-Night Carnival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Beijing will hold a dusk-to-dawn
carnival on Tiananmen Square starting this evening to mark China's
resumption of exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Over 100,000 people from all walks of life are scheduled to
attend the gala celebration.
</P>
<P>
The seven-hour gathering will feature fireworks, performances
carrying the theme "Beijing Bless You, Hong Kong" and outdoor
concerts. It will begin at 10 p.m. local time and last until the
national flag-raising ceremony at about 5:00 on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The festivities will coincide with the handover ceremony to be
held in Hong Kong at mid-night. Huge TV screens positioned on the
square will give the crowd the opportunity to watch the ceremony.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
