<HEADLINE> URGENT: Qian Qichen Meets with Portuguese FM in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen met with Portuguese Foreign Minister Jaime
Gama at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center here this
morning.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who flew into Hong Kong on Sunday from Beijing for the
Hong Kong handover ceremony at midnight today, is scheduled to
meet with British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook, U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright, Japanese Foreign Minister Yukihiko
Ikeda, Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer, Russian
Foreign Minister Yevgeny Maksimovich Primakov and German Foreign
Minister Klaus Kinkel today.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers are here to attend the Hong Kong handover
ceremony. 
