<HEADLINE> Greece Denounces Killing of Consulate Employee in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Greek Foreign Ministry today
denounced the killing of an employee at the Greek consulate in
Gjirokaster, Albania.
</P>
<P>
Christos Kolas, 30, an ethnic Greek, died after being fatally
wounded Saturday by an armed gang attacking the building.
</P>
<P>
The ministry today said in an announcement that Athens could
not but express its "abhor" over such acts, which beyond their
criminal nature, opposed efforts by the international community in
Albania, in which Greece played a leading part.
</P>
<P>
Greek President Costis Stephanopoulos today also expressed
grief at the shooting death of Kolas.
</P>
<P>
After the incident, the Greek government strongly demanded more
effective protection for the general consulate in order to ensure
its normal function and bring an end to a series of assaults by
armed gangs in Albania where the general elections are being
held. 
</P>
</TEXT>
