<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Economic Coordination Pact Proposed at Athens Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The socialist finance ministers
from European Union (EU) member states today proposed that an
economic coordination pact be signed in order to coordinate
efforts related to EU economic policy and to counterbalance the
German-inspired stability and development pact.
</P>
<P>
Greek National Economy and Finance Minister Yiannos Papantoniou
said at a press conference that the proposed economic coordination
was put together with the decisive contribution of the former
European Commission President Jacques Delors, who is currently the
head of the research group "Our Europe."
</P>
<P>
Delors would be willing to exercise his influence with German
Chancellor Helmut Kohl in an effort to convince him to accept the
pact aimed at abolishing the political vacuum in which the
European central bank would operate at the risk of following an
"autonomous monetary policy," Papantoniou said.
</P>
<P>
The ministers wanted to upgrade the council of national economy
and finance ministers (ECOFIN) so that the politicians, and not
the bankers and technocrats, would be making the end decisions
regarding the union's economic policy.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the German central bank and Kohl's ruling
party constitute the strongest opposition to plans by the EU's
socialist ministers to place the European central bank under
political control.
</P>
<P>
The ministers, who gathered here for a two-day conference on
economic and social developments, also said in a communique that
they agreed to finding more resources in order to finance major
infrastructure projects as well as the union's small and
medium-sized businesses which employ two thirds of Europe's labor
force.
</P>
<P>
They also stressed the need for more active policies to boost
employment and fresh motives to help the unemployed find new jobs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970630.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese in Moscow Celebrate Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 29 (Xinhua) -- More than two thousands Chinese
gathered in Moscow on Sunday to celebrate their happy event -- the
return of Hong Kong to its motherland, which is to realize on July
1.
</P>
<P>
The celebration held in the "People's Threat" of "Izmailovsky
Hotel" started with the Chinese national anthem, when all the
people in the hall stood up.
</P>
<P>
On one side of the hall there was a red silk banner with
more than one thousand signatures of overseas Chinese in Moscow,
which is to be passed to the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HK SAR) on the day of the return of Hong Kong to China.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the beginning of the celebration, the charge'
d'affairs ad interim of the Chinese embassy Guan Hengguang noted
that since ancient time Hong Kong was a part of Chinese territory.
Hong Kong's problem was completely caused by Britain which forced
China to accept three unequal treaties.
</P>
<P>
"Thanks to our great leader Deng Xiaoping, who put forward the
great concept of `one country, two systems' and through long and
tough negotiations with the English side, Hong Kong at last
returns to its motherland", Guan said.
</P>
<P>
This event, he continued, means that China washes off its shame
of more than one hundred years and a victory of the great concept
of "one country, two systems".
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Moscow union of the overseas Chinese Zou
Hougong also expressed his excitement on behalf of the overseas
Chinese. He said "one day later, Hong Kong will return to the
embrace of its motherland, and we have the same happy mood with
1,300 million Chinese people." "Let us cheer ! Let us enjoy !" he
acclaimed with excited voice.
</P>
<P>
During the celebration Chinese actors and some Russian
actresses offered brilliant programs for the evening party,
including recitation of poems, singing, dancing, Beijing and local
operas, modern drama and so on.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the performance all the participants loudly sang
the famous song "Sing For Our Motherland". The hall was full of
lively and warm atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
The performances were followed by fireworks display and a film--
"The Opium War". Then, the great celebration was concluded with
dance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
